From 0baea7fe793ed1cd6a9437cf61d0963087e439b0 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Alexander Hoffman <alxhoff@gmail.com>
Date: Mon, 23 Mar 2026 14:50:27 +0100
Subject: [PATCH 10/43] vi5_fops: Fix memory leaks and improve error recovery
 lifecycle

- Remove CSI event sync from error recovery path that caused NULL
  pointer dereference and kernel panic during channel teardown
- Free DMA capture request and embedded data buffers in stop_streaming
  to prevent memory leak on repeated stream start/stop cycles
- Add status code logging to corr_err messages for better diagnostics
  of CSI packet errors
- Improve channel teardown ordering in error_recover to properly stop
  kthreads before releasing hardware resources
---
 .../media/platform/tegra/camera/csi/csi.c     |   6 +-
 .../media/platform/tegra/camera/vi/vi5_fops.c | 117 +++++++++++++-----
 kernel/nvidia/include/media/mc_common.h       |   2 +
 3 files changed, 92 insertions(+), 33 deletions(-)

